content: I think these tips are really helpful, especially the Eisenhower Matrix and allocating time blocks. I've been trying to do too much myself and it's been overwhelming. I need to focus on high-leverage activities and delegate or outsource tasks that take up too much of my time. By the way, speaking of focusing on high-leverage activities, I realized that I decided to start my own business on February 10th, and it's been a wild ride ever since.
